document_data.History:
The usual way of destroying a balhiir, per [[Elminster]], required five mages tearing it apart telekinetically; the process likely killed many of them.{{cite book/Spellfire/Paperback 1988|132_133|8}}{{cite book/Spellfire/Paperback 2005|137|8}}

[[Erimmator]], a mage of the [[Cult of the Dragon]], bound a balhiir to an enemy mage, [[Garthond Shessair]], on or around {{yearlink|1339}}If Shandril is 17 winters old at the end of ''Spellfire'', she would have been conceived sometime around 1339. for the purpose of draining his foe's magic.{{cite book/Heroes' Lorebook|47}} Years later, [[Elminster]] came to suspect it was an experiment to test whether Garthond's offspring would be born with the ability to unleash spellfire.{{cite book/Spellfire/Paperback 1988|356-357|16}}{{cite book/Spellfire/Paperback 2005|365-366|20}}

[[Shandril Shessair]] released a balhiir in {{yearlink|1357}} from a [[balhiir-globe]]{{cite book/Spellfire/Paperback 1988|121|7}} she smashed into the face of the [[Shadowsil]], an enemy sorceress, while trapped in the lair of the [[dracolich]] [[Rauglothgor]]; the balhiir then disrupted the magic of the sorceress, the dracolich, the [[Knights of Myth Drannor]], and of [[Narm Tamaraith]].{{cite book/Cult of the Dragon|23}} The balhiir was recognized by [[Florin Falconhand]], who also revealed the superstition only the one who released the balhiir could slay it.{{cite book/Spellfire/Paperback 1988|102-108, 110|6}}{{cite book/Spellfire/Paperback 2005|101-106, 112-115|6}} The balhiir also annihilated the dracolich's phylactery,{{cite web/Candlekeep Forum/Questions for Ed Greenwood (2006)/01-21 - The Dracoliches in Spellfire}} and much of the magic in the hoard.{{cite book/Spellfire/Paperback 1988|146|9}}{{cite book/Spellfire/Paperback 2005|153|9}} Prompted by [[Elminster]] and with the aid of Narm Tamaraith, who employed the ''[[belch]]'' cantrip upon her to draw the balhiir's attention, she bound it back upon herself,{{cite book/Spellfire/Paperback 1988|115-117|7}}{{cite book/Spellfire/Paperback 2005|117-120|7}} awakening her latent spellfire in the process.

The Shadowsil escaped and warned [[Aghazstamn]] of the balhiir, when seeking his aid against the [[Knights of Myth Drannor]].{{cite book/Spellfire/Paperback 1988|128|8}}{{cite book/Spellfire/Paperback 2005|132|8}} After the battle, Elminster was surprised by the power the balhiir had absorbed,{{cite book/Spellfire/Paperback 1988|121|}}{{cite book/Spellfire/Paperback 2005|125|}} but then judged Shandril released far more power than the creature could have possibly been holding;{{cite book/Spellfire/Paperback 1988|199|11}}{{cite book/Spellfire/Paperback 2005|208|12}} he later confirmed she became able to use spellfire independently of the balhiir.{{cite book/Spellfire/Paperback 1988|233|12}}{{cite book/Spellfire/Paperback 2005|244|14}}
